Class ImageFile

java.lang.Object
  java.io.File
      mickel.image.ImageFile
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Comparable<File>
public class ImageFile
extends File

An abstract representation of a graphics image file (GIF, JPEG, or PNG).

Constructor Detail

ImageFile

public ImageFile(File parent,
                 String child)
Creates a new ImageFile instance from a parent abstract pathname and a child pathname string. Behavior is consistent with the corresponding constructor in the File class. This class is compatible with the following image file formats:

  • GIF

  • JPEG

  • PNG

Parameters:
parent - The parent abstract pathname
child - The child pathname String
Throws:
UnsupportedImageFormatException - if file extension is invalid

ImageFile

public ImageFile(String pathname)
Creates a new ImageFile instance by converting the given pathname string into an abstract pathname. If the given string is the empty string, then the result is the empty abstract pathname.

Parameters:
pathname - The pathname String
Throws:
UnsupportedImageFormatException - if file extension is invalid

ImageFile

public ImageFile(URI uri)
Creates a new ImageFile instance by converting the given file URI into an abstract pathname. Behavior is consistent with the corresponding constructor in the File class.

Parameters:
uri - An absolute, hierarchical URI
Throws:
UnsupportedImageFormatException - if file extension is invalid

createDisplay

public JFrame createDisplay(String title)
Generates a resizable JFrame containing the image represented by this ImageFile. Double-clicking on the image will cause the window to return to its original size.

Parameters:
title - The title bar text for the JFrame window
Returns:
The JFrame containing the specified image
